  "prompt": "Has a game developer set a precedent by allowing others to upload a video to YouTube of a user playing one of his games?",
  "response": "Yes, numerous game developers have set a precedent by allowing users to upload videos of gameplay to platforms like YouTube. This practice has become increasingly common and is often encouraged by developers, as it can serve as free advertising and help build a community around their game. Many developers and publishers even provide explicit guidelines about what content can be shared and under what conditions, and some offer monetization rights under certain circumstances.\n\nFor example, companies like Mojang (creators of Minecraft), Nintendo, and many others have specific policies regarding the sharing of gameplay videos. These policies can vary, so it's always important for content creators to check the guidelines for each specific game or publisher.",
